properties.areaDesc: Northern Humboldt Coast; Southwestern Humboldt; Mendocino Coast; Coastal Del Norte
properties.headline: Beach Hazards Statement issued January 30 at 5:02AM PST until January 30 at 9:00PM PST by NWS Eureka CA
properties.description:
* WHAT...A building westerly swell will result in both large
breaking waves of 17 to 20 feet and an enhanced threat of
sneaker waves on area beaches.

* WHERE...Coastal Del Norte, Northern Humboldt Coast,
Southwestern Humboldt and Mendocino Coast Counties.

* WHEN...Through this evening.

* IMPACTS...Building surf and potentially sneaker waves may create
locally hazardous conditions on area beaches today.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...A sneaker wave is a wave that washes
unexpectedly far up the beach, often after a long period of much
smaller waves before it. Sneaker waves can easily catch people
off guard, and are very dangerous and often deadly due to the
cold, turbulent ocean waters.
properties.instruction:
Maintain a safe distance from the surf, and always keep your eye
on the ocean. Also, remain out of the water to avoid hazardous
swimming conditions, and avoid walking on rocks or jettys.

NWSheadline: BEACH HAZARDS STATEMENT IN EFFECT THROUGH THIS EVENING
